* Prowl seemed to be using the beast instead of himself, relying in it's 
instincts instead of his thoughts.
< Just like me when I just started.> she thought to herself while she moved 
through the ash, black armor melding in perfectly in with it as she began to 
step into a trot, moving more quickly towards Menasor.
It wasn't long before he came into view, sure that Prowl was behind her and 
ready to strike the seconds her mind gave the very signal to her own muscles 
to bunch.*
